This paper is primarily focused on object localization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a modified routing-by-agreement algorithm, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of sparse representation, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is trained on a dataset, which involves neural networks (cs.NE), and the paper also mentions the KTH dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
